## TL;DR: What Every Emerald Cut Ring Buyer Must Know First

The emerald cut engagement ring is different from every other ring. The stone's rectangular outline is not just a shape. It is the design. Your setting choice either serves that outline or fights it.

Most buyers choose a setting that fights it.

**The one thing:** A round pavé halo is the wrong setting for an emerald cut. It puts a soft circular border around a clean rectangle. The emerald cut's best feature — its clean sharp outline — disappears inside it. Solitaire or pavé band is the right setting for this shape.

**Full ring price snapshot (certified market data, {{year}}):**
- Natural 1ct GIA D-VS1 + [Riviera Pavé WG $1,515](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/riviera-pave-diamond-band-engagement-ring-in-18k-white-gold-item-195326?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) = **$4,655 total ring**
- Lab 2ct IGI F-VVS1 + [Petite Solitaire WG $1,115](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/petite-four-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-in-18k-white-gold-item-194979?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) = **$3,344 total ring**
- Lab 2ct IGI D-FL Ideal + [Riviera Pavé WG $1,515](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/riviera-pave-diamond-band-engagement-ring-in-18k-white-gold-item-195326?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) = **$6,250 total ring**

→ **Start here.** Pair a [lab 2ct IGI F-VVS1 emerald cut](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) with the [Petite Four-Prong Solitaire WG at $1,115](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/petite-four-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-in-18k-white-gold-item-194979?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Total: **$3,344.** Two carats of certified lab diamond, 18K white gold, clean silhouette. Nothing at this price comes close.

**Priority:** Choose your setting before you choose your stone. Your setting determines what your stone needs to be. Know The Total Ring Number first. Then buy.

