## Natural Emerald Cut Engagement Ring Prices

Natural GIA-certified emerald cut diamonds in certified market inventory start around $3,000 for a 1ct stone at good quality grades. D colour at 1ct natural starts significantly higher. The emerald cut's large open table shows body warmth more clearly than any brilliant cut — buyers paying for D colour are paying to make sure that open window looks completely colourless.

[![Emerald cut diamond engagement ring yellow gold solitaire with melee band](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioPackshotBox/Rings/501150/501150_M1_EMR_DIM_wht_0100CT_Y_Box5_003_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Emerald&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

<table class="dc-custom-table"><thead><tr><th>Diamond</th><th>Cert</th><th>Colour / Clarity</th><th>Stone Price</th><th>+ Riviera Pavé WG $1,515</th><th>Total Ring</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational">1ct Natural Emerald</a></td><td>GIA</td><td>D / VS1</td><td><strong>$3,140</strong></td><td>+ $1,515</td><td><strong>$4,655</strong></td></tr><tr><td><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational">1.5ct Natural Emerald</a></td><td>GIA</td><td>E / VS1</td><td><strong>$10,409</strong></td><td>+ $1,515</td><td><strong>$11,924</strong></td></tr><tr><td><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational">2ct Natural Emerald</a></td><td>GIA</td><td>F / VS1</td><td><strong>$24,407</strong></td><td>+ $1,515</td><td><strong>$25,922</strong></td></tr><tr><td><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational">3ct Natural Emerald</a></td><td>GIA</td><td>F / VS1</td><td><strong>$63,574</strong></td><td>+ $1,515</td><td><strong>$65,089</strong></td></tr></tbody></table>

**Reading this table.** The 1ct D-VS1 at $4,655 total is the entry for buyers who want the highest colour grade in natural. VS1 is not optional for emerald cuts — it's the floor. The step-cut open table acts like a mirror. SI1 inclusions that a brilliant cut would hide behind its sparkle are clearly visible in an emerald cut. Never go below VS1 in natural. Never.

The jump from 1ct ($4,655 total) to 1.5ct ($11,924 total) is $7,269. That is the steepest size step in the natural emerald cut market. The 2ct natural at $25,922 and 3ct at $65,089 are luxury-tier purchases. The price reflects rough scarcity, not just carat weight.

> "The natural emerald cut market is one of the hardest clarity markets to shop. The step-cut facets are mirrors. They show everything inside the stone. I never recommend natural emerald cuts below VS1, not even after HD video review. For 2ct and above, I want VS1 even after the video.
>
> The price jump from 1ct to 1.5ct in natural — from $3,140 to $10,409 for the stone alone — is the steepest single step in the natural emerald cut market. If 1.5ct natural is out of budget, go to 1ct with a better quality grade. Don't stretch to 1.5ct with compromised clarity. The hall-of-mirrors effect needs a clean stone. A VS2 emerald cut at 1.5ct can look foggy instead of elegant." — Farzana Hasan, **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**

