## Lab Emerald Cut Engagement Ring: Where the Real Value Is

Lab-grown emerald cut diamonds at 2ct and above give you the visual size the shape needs. The long, wide face-up at 2ct makes the hall-of-mirrors effect work properly. You can see it across a room.

And you can get that for a fraction of the natural price.

[![Emerald cut diamond engagement ring yellow gold pavé band packshot on white](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioPackshotBox/Rings/501830/501830_M1_EMR_DIM_wht_0100CT_Y_Box4_004_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Emerald&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

A lab 2ct IGI D-FL Ideal emerald cut costs $4,735 as a loose stone. A natural 1ct D-VS1 costs $3,140. The lab stone is physically twice the size and costs only $1,595 more.

